name: Spadix Resplandissant
description:
--Fig.24--
Spadix Resplandissant is a creature from Dulcinea, and exoplanet located 720 light years from Earth, orbiting the star Cervantes.
Spadixes have 2 life cycles in their lives, one as a vegetable on the ground, another as a very agile flying being. They are the most numerous creatures in its galaxy, sprouting up to 10 million a day. The eggs they carry with them fall to the ground when they die, then generating new buds.
Spadix is known for being a very flavored dish, and its meat can cure many diseases even with only one ingestion of the meal.
